<p>In Matlab, I need to format a latex string containing a numeric variable. The string is like: foo1 , where 1 is contained in variable X and must be subscript. </p>  <p>This line works if I write directly the value of variable</p>  <pre><code>str = texlabel('foo_{1}') </code></pre>  <p>I'm wondering how to insert the X instead of the value. In fact this line</p>  <pre><code>str = texlabel('foo_{X}')' </code></pre>  <p>produce, of course, fooX Thanks</p>